1. 113 to 95 King Street, north side, west of and towards Hudson Street, seen from the clearing on the south side where the Standard Statistics Building is to be erected. Nos. 109, 107, 105, 103 are the four old houses with dormer windows; No. 101 has a flat roof. No. 95 adjoins 363 Hudson Street, the corner building. The one-story garage and lunch room at 97-99 King Street is less than ten years old, it occupies the former site of the Wesley
Methodist Episcopal Church. April 23, 1930.

2. 99 to 121 King Street, north side, from west of Hudson Street to the N.E. corner of Greenwich Street, a view taken on the same day as the above and largely overlapping it. No. 115-121 King
Street is the paper box factory at the left. April 23, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.
